South Africa passed another grim COVID-19 milestone on Monday night as the death toll from the respiratory illness passed 30,000. Health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said in a statement that 434 deaths were recorded in the past 24 hours, taking the national death toll to 30,011. Of the newly recorded deaths, 157 were in the Western Cape, 133 were in the Eastern Cape, 71 in KwaZulu-Natal, 36 in Gauteng, 25 in the North West, seven in Limpopo and two in the Free State. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Mkhize said that SA recorded 12,601 new cases of the illness, meaning that there have now been 1,113,349 confirmed cases of Covid-19 identified across SA. The new cases came from 37,419 tests — a positivity rate of 33.7%. KZN is the country’s epicentre, with 66,900 active cases. The Western Cape is next, with 44,343 active cases. Gauteng has 31,188 active cases. 5 Substitutes Approved For League Cup Semi-final, Final Matches S. African Health Union Urges Gov’t To Be Transparent On Vaccine Plan So far, 911,573 recoveries have been recorded, at a recovery rate of 81.9%. (SOURCE: TimesLIVE) SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION